Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

This change requires some discussion.  My reading of the JSON patch standard is that this is an error condition, so returning a 200 would be incorrect.  For the "remove" operation, for example, it says: "It is an error condition if a value at the specified location does not exist." [1]

I'm happy to be corrected, but this doesn't look like a correct change to me.

[1] https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-pbryan-json-patch-04#section-4.2

Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1

Darja, the bug is in updater here: https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/artifacts/updater.py#L41

As you may see if we have simple path without delimiters, then it just sets the value to the object without any checks. I think you should add the check there to validate that the required property exists.

For example this one: https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/artifacts/updater.py#L62
